Field House was renamed
Fitzgerald Field House follow-
ing the assassination of John
Fitzgerald Kennedy, the field
house was indeed later named
in honor of Chancellor
Fitzgerald.

In his dedication speech,
Chancellor Fitzgerald said, “The
plans of the university will
make this more of a campus
university with an increasing
number of students participat-
ing in extracurricular activities.
With this development will
come a. spirit which will com-
mand a loyalty of students,
alumni and friends.

"This great field house, which
we are dedicating tonight, is
an important step in that direc-
tion. ,

This field house is dedicated
to the health and strength of
young men. It is dedicated to
the development of character
through clean competition and
clean living.”

A basketball game followed
the dedication in which the
Panthers beat the previous
year’s Eastern Champs —
Columbia University.

There have been many
improvements to the field house
in the 40—plus years since its
inception. The track-that encir-
cles the basketball court was
originally dirt, as were the pole
vault pits. The track
was replaced with a hard sur-
face.

Upgrades were also imple-
mented in the seating area as
the caliber of Pitt’s basketball
program improved throughout
the years.

There have also been count-
less memories from sporting
events.which have taken place
at the field house over the last
40-plus years.

“My most memorable experi-
ence in the field house was
when Jerome Lane broke the
backboard slamming a dunk
against Providence.” Paul
Hipp (known as Panther Paul)
said.

As plans for the new convoca-
tion center are unveiled and
completed, the Panther basket-
ball and other teams may be
moving from Fitzgerald Field
House, but memories of events
held in the field house will
never be forgotten.

 

